race.comment: ESJAY (3) has hit a purple patch of form putting back-to-back wins together with hoop Franklin being in the saddle on both occasions. Again gets the benefit of his 3kg claim and can easily bring up the hat-trick without surprising. The well-related SILVER WEDDING (12) (full to G1 winner Schwarz) returned to the winners' stall last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Can go right on with the job now. HELLA FAST (5) saves his best form for his home circuit here and is better than recent efforts suggest. Watch for sharp improvement. RUINS OF ROME (11) is drawn to get a cosy run in transit from the inside alley and rates a genuine top-three candidate. KODIAK (4) rounds out the selections in a race with a few chances.
